description: Fragment of a clay tablet, omens, 22 + 11 lines of inscription, Neo-Assyrian. Upper portion, left half, incantations, prayers and directions for ceremonies to be used for the benefit of sick people.

content.value: If a man’s head is full of sweet lesions: you parch pig bristle, salt, coarse flour (and) sheep bone, you shave his head, you anoint it with oil (and) you scatter (the drugs over the anointment). You anoint (his head) with oil, you pound white plant (and) you scatter it (over the anointment). You dry, crush (and) scatter root of @i{errû}-colocynth (over his head). You parch together, pound (and) scatter malt flour, coarse flour (and) sheep bone (over his head). You heat up (and) pound together @i{annuḫaru}-mineral (and) alum over and over again, you anoint (his head) repeatedly with oil (and) you scatter? (the drugs over the anointment). [You roast (and) scatter xx] (over his head). You anoint (his head) [with] vinegar, you pound mint (and) you scatter it (over the anointment). You knead river mud in date juice (and) you put it on as a bandage. You roast @i{kalbānu}-plant, you anoint (his head) with ghee (and) [you put it on as a bandage]. You pound (and) scatter [xxx] (over his head). You pound (and) scatter pomegranate (over his head). You knead sheep dung in beer (and) you put it on as a bandage. You parch (and) pound [xx]x (and) you put it on as a bandage.

content.value: Alternatively, you burn @i{amānu}-salt, you combine copper? patina? (and) alum together, you mix them (all) in vinegar, you bandage him (with the mixture) and you do not remove it for three days. [While] you remove it, you wash him with warm urine, you anoint him with @i{bappiru}?-bread flour? (and) cedar blood, for five days you scatter these drugs (over the anointment and) you bandage him (with them); then he will recover.
